answers.body_markdown:
for the current question there are few ways to approach,
all of them are from the js itself and not from css, here are some:

 1. using the responsive attributes 

    `&lt;Container&gt;
       &lt;Row&gt;
         &lt;Col md={4}&gt;md=4&lt;/Col&gt;
         &lt;Col md={{ span: 4, offset: 4 }}&gt;{md={{ span: 4, offset: 4 }}} 
         &lt;/Col&gt;
        &lt;/Row&gt;.....`

 2. using justify (and the childrens will split evenly on the navbar)

    `&lt;Navbar className=&quot;bg-light justify-content-between&quot;&gt;`
 3. using margin auto on the left side element

    `&lt;nav.link m=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;leftsideelement&lt;/nav.link&gt;.....&lt;nav.link&gt;will be pushed to the right&lt;/nav.link&gt;`

