   e.g. `this.setState({ search: currentValue })`

2.Once state is updated, `componentDidUpdate` will be called. Now, you can make api call in this method.

    componentDidUpdate(prevProps, prevState) {
          if (prevState.search !== this.state.search) { // or compare with `prevState`
            this.onSearchChange(this.state.search);
          }
        }

