I assume you wired well the service in your angular module.  
You should not use `EventEmitter` inside a service, it is a component thing. Instead, use RxJS BehaviorSubject:

    @Injectable()
    export class EditService{
        private usecasedis$: BehaviorSubject&lt;any&gt; = new BehaviorSubject(null);
    
        setUseCaseDes(des:any){
           console.log(&quot;Inside Edit service&quot;+des); 
           this.usecasedis$.next(des);
        }
    
        getUseCaseDes(): Observable&lt;any&gt;{
          return this.usecasedis$.asObservable();
        }
    }

Thing to know about a BehaviorSubject (and Subjects) is that you have to manually unsubscribe in your component:

EditComponent.ts

    ngOnInit() {
        this.EditUseCaseSubscribtion = this.editService.EditUseCase.subscribe(
          (usecasedes:string)=&gt;alert(&quot;usecasedes&quot;+ usecasedes)
        );
    }
    
    ngOnDestroy() {
        this.EditUseCaseSubscribtion.unsubscribe();
    }

