Your date&#39;s format is: `&#39;%b %e, %Y %h:%i:%s %p&#39;`.&lt;br/&gt;
Read more about the parameters you can use in `str_to_date()` [here][1].&lt;br/&gt;
So do the conversion like this:

    select str_to_date(
      &#39;Sep 2, 2019 8:00:00 PM&#39;,
      &#39;%b %e, %Y %h:%i:%s %p&#39;
    ) as Date
See the [demo][2].


  [1]: https://www.w3schools.com/sql/func_mysql_str_to_date.asp
  [2]: https://www.db-fiddle.com/f/evkXULEMENmAFQzmb2G8Ty/0

Looks like a confusion between the variables defined in the layout and for the actual navigation. If I understood you correctly, you would like to send two variables between navigation destinations using an action. Which variables are available as action parameters is defined in your navigation graph, so you need to ensure that in your navigation graph xml something similar to this is included:

    &lt;fragment
        android:id=&quot;@+id/itemFragment&quot;
    ...&gt;
        &lt;argument
            android:name=&quot;item&quot;
            app:argType=&quot;integer&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;argument
            android:name=&quot;shop&quot;
            app:argType=&quot;string&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;/fragment&gt;

As a result, you will have the parameters available to each action that navigate to the `ItemFragment`:

    action = actionItemsFragmentToItemFragment(1,&quot;string&quot;)

You can access the parameters in the ItemFragment using `getArguments()`. Find more details in the [documentation][1].
In the next step, you can use these variables to set them for use in databinding. 


  [1]: https://developer.android.com/guide/navigation/navigation-pass-data#Safe-args

