answers.body_markdown:
Your problem is that you haven&#39;t taken the `event` and `error` as argument, so these will be `undefined`.

So that code:

    reader.onload = function() {
      resolve(event)
    }; 
    reader.onerror = function() {
      reject(error)
    };

Should be:

    reader.onload = function(event) {
      resolve(event)
    }; 
    reader.onerror = function(error) {
      reject(error)
    };

Or, even simpler:

    reader.onload = resolve
    reader.onerror = reject

